    "definitionDraft": "A world model learns an internal, compressed, predictable and interactive representation of an environment, used to simulate and predict how the world changes in response to actions — not merely to continue text or reconstruct pixels.",
    "whyNow": "In 2024–2026 world models became an industry mainline: one camp pushes video generation toward “world simulators” (Sora), another argues autoregressive LLMs lack physics/causality and needs JEPA (LeCun), and a third pursues spatial intelligence / 3D world generation (Fei-Fei Li’s World Labs).",
    "useBoundary": "Focus on whether a model builds a predictable internal representation of the world (JEPA, Genie, video-as-world-simulator, 3D world generation). Exclude pure video-generation aesthetics/quality."
  },
